Bedeutung wird der Beschreibung der italienischen Gesetzgebung zum Kulturgüterschutz, der Entwicklung der italienischen und alliierten Restitutionspolitik und den Kulturgutsverhandlungen mit der Bundesrepublik Deutschland nach dem Krieg eingeräumt.  aThe work comprehensively treats the implications which were associated with the sale of Italian cultural assets to significant personalities of the German Reich – particulary Hitler und Göring – between 1937 and 1942. First of all, the processes within the Italian leadership hierarchy which generally enabled the sale of artworks to Germany – partially in circumvention of the prevailing art protection laws – will be described. The losses of cultural assets after the Italian neutrality declaration in the autumn of 1943 will also be mentioned.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Nov 2021) 0aLawxInternational Law, Foreign Law, Comparative LawxInternational Law, Foreign Law, Comparative Law, other. 0aLawxLaw, other. 4aDeutschland ‹Bundesrepublik›. 4aItalien. 4aKulturgüterschutz. 4aRestitution ‹Kulturpolitik›. 7aLAW / General.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDGBA Law - 2000 - 2014z9783110636208oZDB-23-GLA0 cprintz978389949167840uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978311089386140uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783110893861423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9783110893861/original  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_LAEC  aEBA_DGALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aEBA_STMALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA12STME  aPDA5EBK  aZDB-23-GLAc2000d2014